main event: A UFO was sighted near Moose Lake, Minnesota on 26 July 1960, identified as a blinking object in the sky.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at night and lasted all night,The object was described as a red 'star' and bright light with a circular shape,The University of Minnesota received numerous calls about the sighting,It was later concluded that the object was probably astronomical in nature,The sighting involved one object that appeared to have a down bouncing motion.
sighted object: one circular object, described as a red 'star'
